The paper discusses machine learning approaches and their interaction with information constraints, which are common topics in the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), distributed computing (cs.DC), information theory (cs.IT), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and systems and control (cs.SY). Given that the paper focuses on the fundamental limits of online and distributed algorithms for statistical learning and estimation, it is most likely to belong to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG), followed by distributed computing (cs.DC), information theory (cs.IT), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and systems and control (cs.SY).
